, Communities and Local Government","2018-03-13","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government: Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what proportion of his Department's estate is (a) rented, (b) owned and (c) occupied through any other type of agreement.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","132215"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/861067","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-03-22","<p>The Defra group has been delivering a significant property rationalisation programme since 2010. In that time annual property running costs have reduced from £170m per year to £100m per year. The number of sites will continue to reduce, with a focus on occupying the Government Property Units Hub sites, where it meets operational delivery for the Defra.</p><p> </p><p>The Core Department occupies sites on the following basis:</p><p> </p><ol><li><p>Rented – 97 sites</p></li><li><p>Owned – 26 sites</p></li><li><p>Occupied through other types of agreement (agreements with other Central Government Departments) - 38</p></li></ol>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-03-22T11:10:16.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/861067/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/861067/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/861067/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-03-13","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what proportion of his Department's estate is (a) rented, (b) owned and (c) occupied through any other type of agreement.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","132216"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/861068","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-03-21","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office estate includes non-residential and residential properties in the UK and overseas. The proportion of holdings by tenure type is stated below.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Owned</p></td><td><p>Leased</p></td><td><p>Loaned</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>43%</p></td><td><p>56%</p></td><td><p>1%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-03-21T16:29:56.47Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/861068/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/861068/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/861068/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-03-13","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what proportion of his Department's estate is (a) rented, (b) owned and (c) occupied through any other type of agreement.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","132217"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/861069","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-21","<p>The Department owns two sites and leases four site that are used by the Department and its arm’s length bodies. One of the owned sites is now been used as part of the Parliamentary estate. It is also occupies space in three other buildings through Memorandums of Terms of Occupation with other public sector organisations. The Department also has a retained estate of 28 sites owned by the Department and six that are leased.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2018-03-21T11:57:04.62Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/861069/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/861069/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/861069/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-13","Department of Health and Social Care: Buildings 
