"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/861070","Home Office","false","2018-03-16","<p>The proportion of the Home Office’s estate that is (a) rented, (b) owned and (c) occupied through any other type of agreement is detailed in the table below.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Department</p></td><td><p>Leasehold</p></td><td><p>%</p></td><td><p>Freehold</p></td><td><p>%</p></td><td><p>PFI</p></td><td><p>%</p></td><td><p>Other</p></td><td><p>%</p></td><td><p>MOTO</p></td><td><p>%</p></td><td><p>Total</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Home Office</p></td><td><p>221</p></td><td><p>38.7</p></td><td><p>15</p></td><td><p>2.6</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>0.2</p></td><td><p>275</p></td><td><p>48.2</p></td><td><p>59</p></td><td><p>10.3</p></td><td><p>571</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Note: “other” includes property holdings provided rent free by port operators.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-03-16T14:34:51.38Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/861070/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/861070/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/861070/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-03-13","Home Office: Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what proportion of her Department's estate is (a) rented, (b) owned and (c) occupied through any other type of agreement.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","132219"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/861071","Department for International Development","false","2018-03-20","<p>The Department for International Development has two Headquarters buildings in the UK, 22-26 Whitehall and Abercrombie House, East Kilbride. Both buildings are owned by, and form part of, the UK Government Estate.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-03-20T15:32:16.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/861071/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/861071/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/861071/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-03-13","Department for International Development: Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what proportion of her Department's estate is (a) rented, (b) owned and (c) occupied through any other type of agreement.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","132220"
