"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/861176","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-03-16","<p>This Government is committed to building an economy that works for everyone. Through the National Minimum Wage and the National Living Wage we continue to ensure the lowest paid in our society are fairly rewarded for their contribution to the economy.</p><p> </p><p>The National Minimum Wage (Amendment) 2018 Impact Assessment includes an assessment of the number of people the Government expects to benefit from the planned increase in the National Living Wage to £7.83: <a href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukia/2018/24/pdfs/ukia_20180024_en.pdf" target="_blank">http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukia/2018/24/pdfs/ukia_20180024_en.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Burton","Andrew Griffiths","132323 ; 132324","2018-03-16T14:02:53.263Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/861176/answer","Biography information for Andrew Griffiths","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/861176/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/861176/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-03-13","Living Wage: South West","1","House of Commons","To ask Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy how many people are estimated to benefit from the planned rise in the national living wage to £7.83 in the South West.","false","Biography information for Luke Hall","Thornbury and Yate","Luke Hall","132325"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/861177","Treasury","false","2018-03-21","<p>Since the start of the 2015 Parliament, increases to the personal allowance (up to £11,500 in 2017-18) are expected to cut income tax for 2.7 million individuals in the South West, which includes Gloucestershire and the Parliamentary Constituency of Thornbury and Yate.</p><p> </p><p>These estimates are based on the 2013-14 Survey of Personal Incomes, projected using economic assumptions consistent with the Office for Budget Responsibility’s March 2016 Economic and Fiscal Outlook.</p><p> </p><p>HM Treasury does not publish this information at constituency level or unitary authority level.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","132327 ; 132328","2018-03-21T15:45:17.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/861177/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/861177/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/861177/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-03-13","Income Tax: Thornbury and Yate","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people are estimated to benefit from the rise in the tax free personal allowance during the 2017-2018 financial year in Thornbury and Yate constituency.","false","Biography information for Luke Hall","Thornbury and Yate","Luke Hall","132326"
